RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 99. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 31000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $12,500. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 15 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since September 15 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 (Claiming Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOOTSIE'S GALAXY was roused to the front to press the pace to the quarter pole then took command and drew clear. GOLD CRUSHER went to the early lead on the inside to the quarter pole then was over taken from outside rival but held on to be second best. IN THE ARCH was unhurried around the first turn then raced five wide down the backstretch, tipped in to four wide on the final turn and rallied to be best of the rest. MISSED THE BOAT raced in the middle of the pack down the backstretch then made a mild bid but flattened out. EYE DEE KAY raced near the back down the backstretch then made a three wide bid on the final turn, moved out to four wide in the stretch and improved position late. DRIED PEPPER raced off the pace from the inside through the final turn but failed to menace. SPERLE saved ground to no avail. COUSVINNYSACANUCK raced in the middle of the pack from three wide through the final turn then moved out to four wide into the stretch but didn't make a rally. DOUBLE THUNDER raced near the back and was not a threat.

ENTRY.NAME: Eye Dee Kay
ENTRY.OWNER: Thompson Racing LLC (Stephen Thompson) and OM Racing Stable LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Gold Crusher
ENTRY.COMMENT: early lead, over taken 1/4, second best,

ENTRY.NAME: Missed the Boat
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, mild bid, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Bootsie's Galaxy
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, took command 1/4, drew clear,

Non-winners Of A Race Since October 15 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since September 15 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Condition Eligibility Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KAHAAL sprinted away from the gate to a clear lead and was kept to task in the stretch. ADIEU ACES was off the pace early then launched his three wide bid at the three furlong marker but was no match for the winner. FLOWER CAT tracked the leaders to the turn then made an inside bid on the turn but was outfinished in the stretch. HALF A BUCK raced near the back to the turn while racing on the inside then made a rail bid in the stretch to improve his position in the drive. CLASSIC RED RACER raced in the middle of the pack and failed to menace. CUSTOM PRAYER raced near the back then moved between horses at the three furlong marker and faltered. LOVE TO SINGH trailed the field and was not a factor. PRICED RIGHT was reluctant to load into the starting gate then was hustle along to be off the pace on the backstretch and gave way on the turn.

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders, mild bid turn, outfinished

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 46. Maiden Claiming Purse 18000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRUE CRIMSON stalked the pace from the two path to the final turn then moved out to three wide in upper stretch for a late rally and drew off in the final sixteenth. ALPHIN went to the front to a pressured lead to midway through the final turn then drew clear going into the stretch but was overtaken in the final sixteenth but held on for the place. COLE'S SENSATION vied for the early lead into the first turn then settled off the pace through the final turn, slipped through on the inside and held on for the show. STYLING HOOK pressed the pace from the two path to the end of the final turn and weakened. TINCAN CAT was unruly behind the gate while being reluctant to load then was roused to the to off the pace going five wide into the first turn and raced three wide down the backstretch and was not a factor. SMOOTH CUSTOM was bumped by outside rival leaving the gate then was allowed to settle on the inside, moved up the rail down the backstretch and faltered. ST PIERRE was allowed to settle down the backstretch but was never a threat. GRAYSONS MALAGRA was pinched back at the start and trailed the field through the final turn. A FOOL FOR CARLOS broke inward at the start then lacked room going into the first turn and had to steady slightly, settled in the middle of the pack down the backstretch then dropped back going into the final turn and was eased, walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 93. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 37000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER, TRIAL OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 15 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since September 15 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Claiming Races For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances). Louisiana Bred Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MBAGNICK (CHI) went four wide into the first turn then made a looming three wide bid at the three furlong marker and dueled down the stretch outside of FLEETRIDGE to prevail. FLEETRIDGE pressed the pace from the two path down the backstretch, vied for the lead on the final turn and took a brief lead into the stretch and dueled on the inside of MBAGNICK (CHI) to the wire and was outnodded. SAMMY DANSEUR JR. was a little rank going into the first turn then cut the corner to take a challenged lead to the eighth pole and gave way but held on for the show. WISE VERDICT was allowed to settle while saving ground down the backstretch then slipped up the rail on the final turn to improve his position. BLUE CHEESE saved ground while racing in the middle of the pack down the backstretch then made a mild inside bid on the final turn but was empty in the stretch. EXTIRPATOR raced off the pace to the three furlong maker then gave way. SMART N INTUITIVE raced in the middle of the pack from the two path down the backstretch then retreated. AMERICAN CODE was unhurried and trailed the field.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL CONSORT went to the front to an unchallenged lead and proved best. BARAHIN stalked the pace from the inside down the backstretch then tipped out to three wide into upper stretch for a late run but couldn't catch the winner and was second best. CARLOS' BLAST raced in the middle of the pack from off the rail and was able to pass the tiring rival to move up and hold on for the show. G'S STORM was off a step slow, saved ground while racing in the middle of the pack then made a rail bid in the stretch for a late run to improve position and miss the show. NEW DICE was unhurried down the backstretch then moved up on the inside around the final turn and split horse in mid stretch while making a late run and improved position. LET'S GO RANDOM tracked the leaders to the top of the stretch and weakened. HOMELAND MESSA was never a threat. WEIRD YEAR was always back. BYATHREAD was off the pace down the backstretch and gave way.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS TULSA raced in the middle of the pack down the backstretch then took aim at the leader with a three wide bid at the quarter pole and took command at the sixteenth pole to draw clear. PICKIN ANA GRINNIN went to the front to a clear lead to set the pace and held that position to the top of the stretch and was overtaken in the final sixteenth but was able to hold on for the place. ADDI BUG was allowed to settle near the back down the backstretch and saved ground around the final turn angle out into the stretch for the late run. MISS DARLENE raced in the middle of the pack on the inside to the final turn then moved out to three wide in the stretch but had no impact. MAGNA COLORS was unhurried around the first turn then made up ground through the final turn, went four wide into the stretch but was too little too late. RIOBELLA stalked the pace from three wide to the three furlong marker and weakened. ROSIE'S ANGUS raced in the middle of the pack from three wide but never made a bid.
